mber's as pleasant as May.\n\n- John\n|\nIf you follow, practice and live ‘Ownership’, you have arrived in Life\n\n- Harrish\n|\nHere is a test to find out whether your mission in life is complete. If you’re alive, it isn’t.\n\n- Lauren\n|\nLife is so beautiful that death has fallen in love with it, a jealous possessive love that grabs at what it can.\n\n- Yann Martel, Life of Pi\n|\nThe heights charm us, but the steps do not; with the mountain in our view we love to walk the plains.\n\n- Johann\n|\nI'm a pessimist because of intelligence, but an optimist because of will.\n\n- Antonio Gramsci, Gramsci's Prison Letters\n|\nBirth, life, and death― each took place on the hidden side of a leaf.\n\n- Toni\n|\nWhen the head tries to rule the heart, emotion poisons it.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nWhen your footsteps and thoughts carry you down the same path your heart and soul are directing you, you will know without a doubt that you are headed in the right direction.\n\n- Molly\n|\nIf you can't be happy, Make someone else happy. :)\n\n- Hossmith\n|\nFreedom, I thought, comes only to the successful\n\n- Graham Greene, Travels With My Aunt\n|\nThe Gospel is the good news, not the grouse news. Preaching is not beating, it´s informing in a christlike way.\n\n- Alin\n|\nEven if there were pains in Heaven, all who understand would desire them.\n\n- C.S. Lewis, The Problem of Pain\n|\nWe're all a part of this world, and it's up to us to make this one chance at living - living worth while. But the only way to do that is by doing it together.\n\n- Robert\n|\nIf you are indecisive, make decisions quickly and act in accordance with your decisions you will be able to acquire a new habit\n\n- Sunday\n|\nA teacher can kindle your mind and let you memorize information, but true education is often self-education.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nSuccesses don't teach you much, but mistakes? That's a learning situation.\n\n- Lyle Link, Dave Isay\n|\nSo much of how we think, feel, and live depends on our vision-what we choose to see in any given situation.\n\n- Jocelyn Green, Faith Deployed...Again: More Daily Encouragement for Military Wives\n|\nGoing round and around inside a dryer can be fatal, whereas pasta is rarely fatal. Unless Isabelle makes it.\n\n- Cassandra Clare, City of Bones\n|\nWhen someone says you've changed, it's because you are no longer willing to live your life their way\n\n- Karon\n|\nWhen you see a good person, think of becoming like her/him. When you see someone not so good, reflect on your own weak points.\n\n- Confucius\n|\nWhat if choices were not viewed as right and wrong, but instead as just a variety of life experiences?\n\n- Staci\n|\nUntil this moment, I had not realized that someone could break your heart twice, along the very same fault lines.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, My Sister's Keeper\n|\nIf you want to be strong, exercise; if you want to be wise, study; if you want to be happy, smile; and if you want to be invincible, love.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThere is love of course. And then there's life, its enemy.\n\n- Jean\n|\nI saw my earlier selves as different people, acquaintances I had outgrown. I wondered how I could ever have been some of them.\n\n- Roger Zelazny, The Courts of Chaos\n|\nthe table of elements does not contain one of the most powerful elements that make up our world, and that is the element of surprise.\n\n- Lemony Snicket, The Ersatz Elevator\n|\nThe more risk you can take upfront in life, the better off you will be later.\n\n- Tarun\n|\nIf we mediate on the Scriptures, our minds shall be on Christ Jesus, the Saviour.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nIf time is precious, no book that will not improve by repeated readings deserves to be read at all.\n\n- Thomas Carlyle, Essays on Goethe\n|\nWhen life's got you down, keep your head up... you can't see the ground anyway\n\n- Nicole\n|\nGod, I love a man who reads\n\n- Tiffany Reisz, Seven Day Loan\n|\nWhere there is no hope, there is Christmas. And where there is no Christmas, there is no hope.\n\n- Craig\n|\nThat person in the mirror is just the outside, your earth suit; the real you resides on the inside\n\n- Sunday\n|\nIt's impossible to go through life unscathed. Nor should you want to. By the hurts we accumulate, we measure both our follies and our accomplishments.\n\n- Christopher Paolini, Inheritance\n|\nBut you hate poetry!Yes, but you make me want to write it.\n\n- Cassandra\n|\nWhen you love this world, this world becomes yours.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nLearn, because life is ahead of you. Live, because death is before you. Listen, because wisdom is all around you. Love, because God is inside of you.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThe Challenge in Life is not to have the absence of Fear, but to have the Courage to overcome it.\n\n- RVM\n|\nTrue education will shape your life, but if you ignore education you will be punished by your life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nEvery existing thing is born without reason, prolongs itself out of weakness, and dies by chance.\n\n- Jean-Paul\n|\nHow prone to doubt, how cautious are the wise!\n\n- Homer\n|\nThe Lovely Knowing, your source of intuition and inspiration may not always be explainable, but it is always attainable!\n\n- Mishi\n|\nWake up, Shake up, Make up and Break up; life is all about moving like ant in search of sugar not sand.\n\n- Santosh Kalwar, Quote Me Everyday\n|\nThe true meaning of Religion is to Love God and Man, Hatred is out of the Equation\n\n- Samuel"